\title{Mathpix Ocr}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Mathpix OCR for LaTeX extraction with balanced ternary checkpoints}

\subtree{
\title{mathpix-ocr - Balanced Ternary OCR Pipeline for LaTeX → ACSet Extraction}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{Integrates [TeglonLabs/mathpix-gem](https://github.com/TeglonLabs/mathpix-gem) for mathematical OCR with the music-topos ACSet parallel rewriting system. Uses seed 1069 balanced ternary checkpoints for resilient PDF batch processing.}
}

\subtree{
\title{The 1069 Connection}
\p{mathpix-gem shares our canonical seed:}

\pre{\startverb
# From mathpix-gem/lib/mathpix/balanced_ternary.rb
# 1×3⁶ - 1×3⁵ - 1×3⁴ + 1×3³ + 1×3² + 1×3¹ + 1×3⁰ = 1069
SEED_1069_PATTERN = [+1, -1, -1, +1, +1, +1, +1].freeze

# Semantics progression:
#   +1 (high confidence) → -1 (descent) → -1 (exploration) →
#   +1 (recovery) → +1 (convergence) → +1 (stability) → +1 (completion)
\stopverb}

\p{This maps directly to our TAP states and GF(3) arithmetic.}
}

